1. What kind of data was compromised (identify PII)?
    Customer personal data was compromised which mainly included:
        (1) Names (PII)
        (2) Phone Numbers (PII)
        (3) Aadhaar Numbers (highly sensitive PII because works as National ID)
        (4) Bank Account Details (highly sensitive PII as this may cause financial loses)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. How could this incident have been prevented?
    This type of incident can be prevented by using strict security measures, some of them are:
        (1) Strict Access Controls: Enforce the Principle of least privleage.
        (2) Block Public Access: Enable AWS's "Block Public Access" feature 
            by default.
        (3) Regular Audits: Continuously monitor and audit AWS configurations.
        (4) Developer Training: Educate teams on secure cloud practices and PII handling.
        (5) Infrastructure as Code (IaC): Manage configurations 
            through version-controlled, secure templates.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. What are the immediate and long-term measures the company must take?
    Immediate Measures:
        (1) Containment: Immediately block public access to the bucket and revoke 
            unauthorized credentials.
        (2) Forensics: Preserve logs and  conduct a rapid investigation to determine the 
            breach's scope.
        (3) Notification: Inform affected customers and relevant data protection 
            authorities.

    Long-Term Measures:
        (1) Enhanced Cloud Security Governance: Implement robust policies, 
            automated security tools and continuous monitoring.
        (2) Employee Training: Conduct mandatory and recurring cybersecurity training 
            for all staff.
        (3) Data Minimization: Review and reduce unnecessary collection or we can 
            say retention of PII.
        (4) Incident Response Plan Refinement: Update and regularly test the 
            incident response plan.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------